# Applications.properties

spring.h2.console.enabled=true
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:testdb
spring.datasource.driverClassName=org.h2.Driver
spring.datasource.username=sa
spring.datasource.password=

spring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update
spring.jpa.show-sql=true


H2 Database in Spring Boot is an embedded, open-source, and in-memory database. It is a relational database management system written in Java. It is a client/server application.
It stores data in memory, not persist the data on disk. Here we will be discussing how can we configure and perform some basic operations in Spring Boot using H2 Database.
